ive look at how superhero media shapes our perceptions of love, sex, and gender.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aComic books, strips, etc.xSocial aspects. 0aLove in mass media. 0aSex role in mass media. 0aSuperheroes in mass media. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  asuperheroes, sex, gender studies, comic studies, popular culture, American studies, women's studies, LGBTQ studies, DC, marvel comic.40uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882529140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978825291423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978825291/original  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK